CHANGELOG.md
     1→# Changelog
     2→
     3→## 1.21.3
     8→## 1.21.2
     9→- Relax success ordering from AcqRel to Release in `race`: [#278](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/278).
    11→## 1.21.1
    12→- Reduce MSRV to 1.65: [#277](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/277).
    14→## 1.21.0
    15→
    16→- Outline initialization in `race`: [#273](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/273).
    21→## 1.20.2
    22→
    23→- Remove `portable_atomic` from Cargo.lock if it is not, in fact, used: [#267](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/267)
    26→## 1.20.1
    27→
    28→- Allow using `race` module using just `portable_atomic`, without `critical_section` and provide
    32→## 1.19.0
    33→
    34→- Use `portable-atomic` instead of `atomic-polyfill`, [#251](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/251).
    36→## 1.18.0
    37→
    38→- `MSRV` is updated to 1.60.0 to take advantage of `dep:` syntax for cargo features,
    41→## 1.17.2
    42→
    43→- Avoid unnecessary synchronization in `Lazy::{force,deref}_mut()`, [#231](https://github.com/matklad/once_cell/pull/231).
    45→## 1.17.1
    46→
    47→- Make `OnceRef` implementation compliant with [strict provenance](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/95228).
    49→## 1.17.0
    50→
    51→- Add `race::OnceRef` for storing a `&'a T`.
    53→## 1.16.0
    54→
    55→- Add `no_std` implementation based on `critical-section`,
    59→## 1.15.0
    60→
    61→- Increase minimal supported Rust version to 1.56.0.
    64→## 1.14.0
    65→
    66→- Add extension to `unsync` and `sync` `Lazy` mut API:
    71→## 1.13.1
    72→
    73→- Make implementation compliant with [strict provenance](https://github.com/rust-lang/rust/issues/95228).
    76→## 1.13.0
    77→
    78→- Add `Lazy::get`, similar to `OnceCell::get`.
    80→## 1.12.1
    81→
    82→- Remove incorrect `debug_assert`.
    84→## 1.12.0
    85→
    86→- Add `OnceCell::wait`, a blocking variant of `get`.
    88→## 1.11.0
    89→
    90→- Add `OnceCell::with_value` to create initialized `OnceCell` in `const` context.
    94→## 1.10.0
    95→
    96→- upgrade `parking_lot` to `0.12.0` (note that this bumps MSRV with `parking_lot` feature enabled to `1.49.0`).
    98→## 1.9.0
    99→
   100→- Added an `atomic-polyfill` optional dependency to compile `race` on platforms without atomics
   102→## 1.8.0
   103→
   104→- Add `try_insert` API -- a version of `set` that returns a reference.
   106→## 1.7.2
   107→
   108→- Improve code size when using parking_lot feature.
   110→## 1.7.1
   111→
   112→- Fix `race::OnceBox<T>` to also impl `Default` even if `T` doesn't impl `Default`.
   114→## 1.7.0
   115→
   116→- Hide the `race` module behind (default) `race` feature.
   122→## 1.6.0
   123→
   124→- Add `Lazy::into_value`
   128→## 1.5.2
   129→
   130→- `OnceBox` API uses `Box<T>`.
   133→## 1.5.1
   134→
   135→- MSRV is increased to `1.36.0`.
   140→## 1.5.0
   141→
   142→- add new `once_cell::race` module for "first one wins" no_std-compatible initialization flavor.
   145→## 1.4.1
   146→
   147→- upgrade `parking_lot` to `0.11.0`
   151→## 1.4.0
   152→
   153→- upgrade `parking_lot` to `0.10` (note that this bumps MSRV with `parking_lot` feature enabled to `1.36.0`).
   157→## 1.3.1
   158→
   159→- remove unnecessary `F: fmt::Debug` bound from `impl fmt::Debug for Lazy<T, F>`.
   161→## 1.3.0
   162→
   163→- `Lazy<T>` now implements `DerefMut`.
   166→## 1.2.0
   167→
   168→- add `sync::OnceCell::get_unchecked`.
   170→## 1.1.0
   171→
   172→- implement `Default` for `Lazy`: it creates an empty `Lazy<T>` which is initialized with `T::default` on first access.
   175→## 1.0.2
   176→
   177→- actually add `#![no_std]` attribute if std feature is not enabled.
   179→## 1.0.1
   180→
   181→- fix unsoundness in `Lazy<T>` if the initializing function panics. Thanks [@xfix](https://github.com/xfix)!
   186→## 1.0.0
   187→
   188→- remove `parking_lot` from the list of default features.
   194→## 0.2.7
   195→
   196→- New implementation of `sync::OnceCell` if `parking_lot` feature is disabled.
   201→## 0.2.6
   202→
   203→- Updated `Lazy`'s `Deref` impl to requires only `FnOnce` instead of `Fn`
   205→## 0.2.5
   206→
   207→- `Lazy` requires only `FnOnce` instead of `Fn`
   209→## 0.2.4
   210→
   211→- nicer `fmt::Debug` implementation
   213→## 0.2.3
   214→
   215→- update `parking_lot` to `0.9.0`
   219→## 0.2.2
   220→
   221→- add `OnceCell::into_inner` which consumes a cell and returns an option
   223→## 0.2.1
   224→
   225→- implement `sync::OnceCell::get_or_try_init` if `parking_lot` feature is enabled
   231→## 0.2.0
   232→
   233→- MSRV is now 1.31.1
   237→## 0.1.8
   238→
   239→- update crossbeam-utils to 0.6
   242→## 0.1.7
   243→
   244→- cells implement `PartialEq` and `From`
   248→## 0.1.6
   249→
   250→- `unsync::OnceCell<T>` is `Clone` if `T` is `Clone`.
   252→## 0.1.5
   253→
   254→- No changelog until this point :(
README.md
     8→# Overview
     9→
    10→`once_cell` provides two new cell-like types, `unsync::OnceCell` and `sync::OnceCell`. `OnceCell`
    11→might store arbitrary non-`Copy` types, can be assigned to at most once and provide direct access
    12→to the stored contents. In a nutshell, API looks *roughly* like this:
    47→# Related crates
    48→
    49→* [double-checked-cell](https://github.com/niklasf/double-checked-cell)
    50→* [lazy-init](https://crates.io/crates/lazy-init)
    51→* [lazycell](https://crates.io/crates/lazycell)
    52→* [mitochondria](https://crates.io/crates/mitochondria)
    53→* [lazy_static](https://crates.io/crates/lazy_static)
    54→* [async_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/async_once_cell)
    55→* [generic_once_cell](https://crates.io/crates/generic_once_cell) (bring your own mutex)
